Fix the Android crash when navigating from `app/post-gig.tsx` to the profile tab after posting a gig.

## Root cause
`post-gig.tsx` is a Stack screen (outside tabs). After success, it calls `router.replace('/(tabs)/profile')`. On Android, `router.replace` from a stack screen to a nested tab route is unreliable and causes crashes because expo-router on Android cannot cleanly replace a stack entry with a tabs/nested route.

## Fix in `app/post-gig.tsx`

Change the `handleSuccessClose` function to use a two-step navigation that works reliably on Android:

```tsx
const handleSuccessClose = () => {
  if (!mountedRef.current) return;
  setSuccessModal({ visible: false, title: '', message: '' });

  try {
    // Use push instead of replace to avoid Android navigation state corruption
    // Then use router.navigate which is safer for tab routes on Android
    router.navigate('/(tabs)/profile');
  } catch (navError) {
    console.error('Navigation error:', navError);
    try {
      router.back();
    } catch (e) {
      console.error('Fallback navigation failed:', e);
    }
  }
};
```

Wait — actually the most reliable fix for Android is to use `router.dismissAll()` followed by `router.replace`. But `dismissAll` may not exist in this expo-router version.

The correct fix for expo-router on Android when navigating from a stack screen to a tab is:

```tsx
const handleSuccessClose = () => {
  if (!mountedRef.current) return;
  setSuccessModal({ visible: false, title: '', message: '' });

  // On Android, router.replace to a tab route from a stack screen can crash.
  // Use router.navigate which handles the tab route correctly on both platforms.
  router.navigate({
    pathname: '/(tabs)/profile',
  });
};
```

